name: transforming acidic coiled-coil containing protein 1
summary: This locus may represent a breast cancer candidate gene. It is located close to FGFR1 on a region of chromosome 8 that is amplified in some breast cancers. Several transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for this gene. [provided by RefSeq, Jun 2017].
